canonical:
  title: 神懿王后玉冊文
  author: 卞季良
  language: lzh
  text: 永念至恩不勝感愴追增徽號惟極尊崇祗率舊章用申孝懇恭惟禀資神懿秉心順承德協乾元若塗山之配禹道全恒吉齊太姒之母周嚴敎子之義方篤逮下之仁恩伏念猥承厚澤嗣襲丕基爰卜良辰式陳縟禮伏惟謹遣某官某奉冊上尊謚曰神懿仰惟眧鑑俯諒精衷衍萬世之本支緜億年之曆服
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 神懿王后玉冊文
  author: 卞季良
  language: lzh
  text: 永念至恩。不勝感愴。追增徽號。惟極尊崇。祗率舊章。用申孝懇。恭惟禀資神懿。秉心順承。德協乾元。若塗山之配禹。道全恒吉。齊太姒之母周。嚴敎子之義方。篤逮下之仁恩。伏念猥承厚澤。嗣襲丕基。爰卜良辰。式陳縟禮。伏惟謹遣某官某。奉冊上尊謚曰神懿。仰惟眧鑑。俯諒精衷。衍萬世之本支。緜億年之曆服。
korean:
  title: 신의왕후 옥책문
  author: 변계량
  language: kor
  text: 길이 지극하신 은혜를 생각하여 슬픔을 이기지 못하고, 뒤늦게 아름다운 칭호를 더해 올려서 존숭하는 도리를 다합니다. 이에 삼가 옛 예법을 좇아 효도의 정성을 폅니다.공손히 생각하옵건대, 타고나신 자품은 신성하며 아름다웠고, 마음가짐은 순하며 공손하였습니다. 덕이 건원(乾元)에 협조되시니 도산(塗山)이 우(禹) 임금의 짝이 됨과 같고, 도는 곤괘(坤卦)에 해당하니 태사(太姒)가 주(周)나라의 어머니였던 것과 같았습니다. 자제에게 의방(義方)의 교육을 엄준하게 하시고, 아랫사람에게 은혜를 돈독하게 하셨습니다.엎드려 생각하옵건대, 외람되게 후하신 은택을 받자와, 큰 기업을 계승하여 지키게 되었기에, 길한 날을 가려서 공손히 아름다운 예를 베풉니다. 이에 삼가 모관 모를 보내서 책(冊)을 받들어 존시(尊諡)를 올려 신의(神懿)라 하옵니다. 오직 밝게 내려다 보시어 이 정성을 굽어 살피셔서, 만대의 종손과 지손을 불어나게 하시며, 억만 년토록 국운을 이어 가게 하소서.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0320_010_0150&viewSync=OT
  footnotes:
  - key: '[주-D001] 眧 : '
    value: 昭
english:
  title: Edict Bestowing the Posthumous Title Upon Queen Sinieui
  author: Byeon Gyeyang
  language: eng
  text: |-
    In perpetual remembrance of boundless grace,
    My heart overflows with sorrow I cannot contain.
    I offer this belated honor, elevating her noble name,
    Fulfilling the duty of supreme reverence.
    Following the ancient rites with utmost care,
    I present this expression of filial devotion.

    Reverently I reflect: her nature was divine and beauteous,
    Her spirit gracious and obedient.
    Her virtue harmonized with Heaven's primal force—
    As Tushan was mate to the great Yu,
    Her way encompassed the Receptive principle—
    As Taisi was mother to the Zhou dynasty.
    With rigorous wisdom she taught her children,
    With benevolent compassion she succored the humble.

    Humbly I consider: unworthy as I am,
    I have received such abundant favor,
    Inheriting and preserving this great legacy.
    On this auspicious day, I perform these solemn rites with reverence.
    I respectfully dispatch the officials bearing the imperial seal,
    To present this edict conferring the posthumous title: Sinieui.

    May Heaven's bright gaze look down upon this sincere devotion,
    Extending the lineage through ten thousand generations,
    That her blessings flow eternal through countless ages.
  footnotes:
    - Tushan and Taisi reference the archetypal wise consorts of Chinese antiquity—the former aided Yu the Great in controlling the Great Flood, the latter was the virtuous mother of the Zhou dynasty's founders.
    - The 'Receptive principle' (坤卦) refers to the yin principle of the I Ching, symbolizing receptivity, support, and maternal virtue.
